topic.title: Recovered Clock Selection (PGMRCLK)

body.p: * The PGMRCLK[7:0] device pin outputs are each connected to a N:1 clock mux where all of the possible clock sources are shown in Table 1 for the different values of FDIV_(7:0)_CLK_SELECT[8:0].

li.p: There are 8 separate FDIV_(7:0)_CLK_SELECT[8:0] registers corresponding to each of the PGMRCLK[7:0] device outputs. Use the values in this table to configure each output from the provided selection.

There are eight separate LINE_DSIS M1_CLK_OUT_SEL[7:0] values corresponding to each of the PGMRCLK[7:0] device outputs. Use the values in this table to configure each output from the provided selection.
When configuring LINE_DSIS M1_CLK_OUT_SEL[7:0], FDIV_(7:0)_CLK_SELECT[8:0] must also be set to 511.
